modules.description: This module transforms JSX syntax into OCaml AST structures through operations like argument label normalization, child expression rewriting, and attribute-to-prop conversion. It manipulates core OCaml AST nodes—including expressions, value bindings, and module declarations—to enable ReactJS component compilation and external module integration. Key use cases include JSX-to-OCaml transpilation, prop type inference, and generating React-ready component declarations with labeled arguments and configuration payloads.
